// =============================================================================
// Modulus — EXPENSIVE. The floor-mod family, derived from the SAME
// eigenrotation that powers sin/cos in math.su.
// =============================================================================
//
// Read math.su first: cos/sin are the real/imag parts of the unit
// eigenrotation by an angle. Modulus is that same rotation, but around a
// circle whose CIRCUMFERENCE is the modulus m instead of 2π.
//
// ── Why modulus is an eigenrotation ─────────────────────────────────────────
//
// Walking distance x around a circle of circumference m and asking "where
// did I end up" IS `x mod m`. Map the walk to an angle, rotate, read the
// phase back, scale the phase by m/2π:
//
//   θ      = 2π · x / m              (x scaled so one lap = m)
//   (c, s) = cos θ, sin θ            (the eigenrotation — math.su leaves)
//   φ      = atan2(s, c)             (phase of the rotated vector)
//   φ_pos  = φ - 2π·floor(φ / 2π)    (re-wrap onto [0, 2π))
//   result = m · φ_pos / (2π)        (un-scale: angle back to distance)
//
// The rotation is intrinsically periodic — `R(θ + 2π) = R(θ)` exactly — so
// the modulus "comes for free" from the rotation; there is no separate
// range-reduction step. This is `_VSA.rotation_mod`, all tensor ops, and
// the language's canonical `mod`. (`atan2` is still a tensor op; replacing
// it with its own eigenrotation lookup is the one tracked follow-on in the
// substrate-leak audit.)
//
// floor / ceil / round / trunc / abs / sign are NOT transcendental
// decompositions — they are native substrate (GPU) rounding instructions,
// one tensor op each, so they sit at the primitive layer beside +, -, *.
//
// All are `intrinsic` (route to substrate-pure `_VSA.*`). The ideal form
// — Sutra bodies like `static method scalar mod(...) {
// return Math.rotation_mod(x, m); }` so the substitution is the source
// itself — is blocked on the same stdlib-inliner limitation documented in
// math.su (intra-`Math` member calls inside a class-bodied static method
// body don't resolve yet). Tracked at the top of the substrate-leak audit.
//
// These extend `class Math` so JS-shaped call sites (`Math.floor(x)`,
// `Math.abs(x)`) merge into one namespace via the stdlib loader. `%`
// lowers to `Math.fmod` (truncation modulus, sign of the dividend);
// `Math.mod` is the eigenrotation floor-mod (non-negative for m > 0).

class Math extends vector {

    // ── Native substrate rounding instructions ───────────────────────────────
    //
    // Each is a single tensor op in _VSA (torch.floor / ceil / round /
    // trunc / abs / sign), tensor-in → tensor-out, no host scalar.
    static intrinsic method number floor(number x);
    static intrinsic method number ceil(number x);
    static intrinsic method number round(number x);
    static intrinsic method number trunc(number x);
    static intrinsic method number abs(number x);
    static intrinsic method number sign(number x);

    // ── The eigenrotation modulus ────────────────────────────────────────────
    //
    // rotation_mod — the chain documented in the header. Substrate-pure:
    //   cos/sin eigenrotation + atan2 + re-wrap, all tensor ops. Always
    //   non-negative for m > 0 (`Math.rotation_mod(-0.1, 1) == 0.9`);
    //   discontinuous at integer multiples of m (atan2 branch cut).
    //   Divisor 0 → NaN tensor, the degenerate limit, not a host raise.
    static intrinsic method number rotation_mod(number x, number m);

    // sawtooth_mod — the smooth Fourier-series alternative:
    //   mod_floor(x,m) ≈ m/2 − (m/π)·Σ_{k=1..N} sin(2πkx/m)/k. The k-sum
    //   is a single vectorized tensor reduction (a (K,N) crosstalk-weight
    //   matmul against the sin table), NOT a Python loop. Fully
    //   differentiable; ~9% Gibbs ring near integer multiples of m.
    static intrinsic method number sawtooth_mod(number x, number m);

    // fmod — truncation modulus (JS / C / C# / Rust / TS `%`): result has
    //   the sign of the dividend. x − m·trunc(x/m), all tensor ops.
    //   Divisor 0 → NaN tensor (no host ZeroDivisionError). `%` lowers
    //   here.
    static intrinsic method number fmod(number x, number m);

    // mod — the canonical mathematical floor-modulus. _VSA.mod is a
    //   direct alias of _VSA.rotation_mod (`mod = rotation_mod`): the
    //   substitution is the identity. Non-negative for m > 0
    //   (`Math.mod(-0.1, 1) == 0.9`). This is what mathematical code
    //   should reach for; `%` (fmod) keeps the dividend's sign for JS
    //   parity.
    static intrinsic method number mod(number x, number m);
}
